        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Pin managed Linux bootstrap installers",
        "body": "Closes #715.\n\nManaged Linux bootstrap no longer emits root `curl | sh` installer pipelines for Code or Tailscale. Code-server installs from pinned release tarballs with SHA-256 verification, and Tailscale always uses the checksum-verified static archive path.\n\nCompatibility note: legacy `CRABBOX_TAILSCALE_INSTALL_MODE=package` now maps to the pinned static archive path; preserving package-mode semantics would require a separate signed repository path.\n\nProof: Worker and Go bootstrap regressions assert verified archive installs and absence of the old installer-script URLs.",
